{
  "stem": "1502.6",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was taken--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I was taken to the flitzer cell, to the place where the escapees were.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there I met another gentleman that I did not know, but he was from Brussels also, and he was a real escapee.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because in 1943, the Jewish underground attacked a train that was going from Mechelen to Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They attacked a train, and some people were killed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was shooting between the German guards of the train and the Jewish underground.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's was right before Passover 1943.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the niece of this particular man-- his name was Silbershwartz-- his niece was killed in the escape.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But it was a grand escape.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Maybe 200 or 300 people escaped from that train, and he was one of them.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was caught in a hiding place a year later.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They had him on the record that he escaped.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he was put-- he was my neighbor, and we became very friendly with-- with-- we're together.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The-- the commander-- the Jewish commander of the camp, the lagerfuhrer, Mayer, continued to protect me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The letter came from the headquarters and the Gestapo that I should do the dirtiest work in camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The dirtiest work, what he gave me to do, was, you know, in the-- during the night, people to go to the bathroom.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So they had in the each hole, they had a big, a kind of, of a pot, of a bottle, huge.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that was for 100 people, for whatever they had to do during the night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I was ordered to take these out from each of the holes, and to take it out and take care of it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "That was my job and punishment.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But it was a pretty good exchange for the bunker.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
